pan><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">MG15(T)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> forms</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, Exhibit lists, forge </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">C&amp;D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> signature, re-type all transcripts,  re-stamp all paginatio</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n and stamp Exhibit Nos with a stamp they probably don’t possess?</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The alleged conspiracy is not over.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">After </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">report</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">alleged </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">forgery </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as a crime in 2012 two more Gwent officers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">wrote to protect their colleagues</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">then </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">refused further correspon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dence</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">So much for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a few of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">document</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">facts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as I see them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The implications </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and questions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are so diverse I cannot get my head round them.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Interpretations, I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">mplications</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> and Comments</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The innocent suffer most.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This is a case of bullying, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(a)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> not of a whistleblower, but a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">potential whistleblower</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(b)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">his estranged wife</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and her children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> who</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> have, and had, nothing to do with Tshire Police or their crime statistics.  They lived 240 miles away.  They are powerless to battle against the pilla</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rs of the criminal justice system</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, the very people employed to maintain standards and protect them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliament allows no challenge to an IPCC conclusion except JR.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">How can they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">afford</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> justice?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What can PWB do?</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Responsible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">profession</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">als appear </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">crimin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ally </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">collusive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">My allegations, mostly of perverting justice, are against </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">up to 20 members from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Tshire’s Complaints and Discipline Department, its Standards Department, ACPO officers, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PA, HMIC, the IPCC, the Home Office and the P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There needs to be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> an impartial investigation, but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">none of these organisations can be trusted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to do it</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">None has shown moral integrity.  Who should take responsibility now?  The Home Secretary?</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">19</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What motiv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ates</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> members of these organisations to collude?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">How </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and why</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">does this conspiracy work?  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Do all the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> people </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">involved </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">know each other?  I doubt it.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yet they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">protect each other.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They don’t know Mrs PWB either</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but there is no loyalty to her.  S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he doesn’t matter to them.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">L</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ike racism,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ‘She’s not one of us’.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">20</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">A </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">placed loyalty and power are prioritised above truth and justice.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Psychologists call this phenomenon, ‘Groupthink’.  It commonly unites bullying groups.  It is characterised by pressures to conform, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">perceived </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">safety in group membership, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a sense of power, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ationalised self justification,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a belief in group unanimity, self censorship, belittlement of others</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, self denial, a belief in their own morality and sometimes ‘mindguards’ who actively prevent expression of dissent.  There may also be laziness: ‘It must b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e OK if all those people think so’.  Arguably Hillsborough and Met Police also offer examples.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">21</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">‘Collusion’ or ‘corruption’?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">By saying “collusion” I have carefully stopp</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed short of saying “corruption”.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">But when </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">those </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in positions of governmental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">public service</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> protect each other</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in breaking the law</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">then use their position and power to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pressure conform</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ity by others,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that the essence of a corrupt state</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I cannot prove it, but w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hatever the word, if the paperwork had fallen </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">governmen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> desk</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> I believe the forces of ‘Groupthink’ would have applied just the same</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  It is too much for me to believe a remarkable coincidence that the paperwork always fell to collusively vulnerable individuals.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">And that is all the more alarming because mos</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t of the individuals in question are in senior positions.  If the media asked me, ‘How near is corruption to the top of these governmental institutions?’ I should have difficulty in giving rational assurance.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The neglected moral values of policing.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  Part of the problem is that the police, public and government have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a one-sided </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">TV </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">view</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of what policing should be.  The police are seen as an organisation responding to incidents, catching and prosecuting offenders.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These are the values of power.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of course</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">police should offer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> far more than that.  Police should offer protection and the provision of needs. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Many do.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These are the values of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">care, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">compassion and service.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PWB </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and his family </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">got none of that.  Police need both.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Whit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">her reform? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o who is in any position to change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> this unprofessional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">collusive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">counter-culture</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> No one.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Individuals have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to change </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">themselves</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  Chang</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> values cannot be imposed.  Opportunities can be created, that is all.  It is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a massive task.  The f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">irst step is Truth and Reconciliation using </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the methods of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Restorative Justice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Without them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> do we have a long inquiry and even longer </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">criminal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">trials?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  And what would th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ey</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> do?  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We need procedures that can support a culture in changing itself. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> That seems lacking.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Attitude change is by far the most difficult task in adult education.  It needs taking empl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">yees out of their comfort </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">zone for say two weeks, requiring them to decide upon ambiguous decision scenarios, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">indentifying and clarifying in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">iscussion the moral principles implied</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the beginning of each day </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">devoted to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> shared inner reflection in a group of up to 30 similarly engaged.  I have done this work when re-training police trainers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  It requires very careful of preparation of scenario</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s, but can be rewarding in the long run.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">23</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Statistics for Domestic Violence should be distinguished from other VAP.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Crimes per population could aid interpretation.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I believe what began with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">suspicious crime statistics </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has led to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a long ru</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nning criminal conspiracy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> amongst relatively senior members of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">police related professions.  There is no effective redress for its victims.  Correspondence shows the police know that and trade upon it.  Thus there is power without adequate restraint, a reci</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pe for corruption.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Secrecy is the vehicle of conspiracy.  I believe its </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legitimised use is excessive and needless</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ore than statistics</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ultimately it is these issues and flaws in procedures that need parliamentary attention.  </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>